  {
    "client_msg_id": "5c5d2a96-d197-436b-9539-972d5f57780d",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Couple of things looked strange about your example at first glance.\n\n* You have to keep adding rows to your light object as you add features.\n* The rule is in its own row. Why not have the value of brightness contain a rule? That's more spreadsheet like. I suppose you lose the ability to have rules make multiple changes at once.\n\nThe big thing in Onex seems to be giving spreadsheet formulae their own place, so that they can be modified themselves. That's more powerful, but it's hard to reconcile with the first half where you suggest it's easier to use. I think it'll be easier to screw up, and programs will turn into spaghetti faster than spreadsheets.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1562433220.141200",
